Private attributes - accessible only within the class
Here name is private, so no one can access it directly. Instead, we provide public methods called getters and setters to safely access or modify it.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

class access{
    private String name;
    int roll;
    public void display(){
        System.out.println("Name: "+name);
        System.out.println("Roll No.: "+roll);
    } 
    public void setvalue(String str,int num){
        name=str;
        roll=num;
    }
    public String getvalue(){
        return name;
    }
}
public class AccessModifier {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        /*AppForm_within addmission2=new AppForm_within();
        in.nextLine();
        System.out.print("Name: ");
        addmission2.name=in.nextLine(); //error occurs as directly accessing the name which is private 
         */

        //using getter and setter function to access private attribute
        access addmission1=new access();
        addmission1.setvalue("maha", 215); //not accessing name directly but passing the value to access name
        addmission1.display();
        System.out.println("I");
        // System.out.println(addmission1.name); //error arise as the name is not visible to main class
        System.out.println("Roll no :"+addmission1.roll); //gives 215
        //to get the value of name in accessModifier class use getvalue
        System.out.println("Name: "+addmission1.getvalue());
    }
}
